Text.Value: Shrug.
Let's go. We have a city to save.
You sound like you speak from experience.
Karlach deserves a better end than twisting herself into flayer-form. But then, she deserves a long life, too.

EditorData.NodeContext: Grim, does not like Karlach's decision to sacrifice herself and become a mind flayer - but knows it's our only option

Text.Value: Agreed. I have been spending too much time with the wild and rebellious youth.
Not really in the mood for jokes, Jaheira. Sorry.
I don't know, Jaheira. This is all new to me.

This world is a better place with you in it, for as little or as long as it is lucky enough to have you. It is most certainly a better place without Enver Gortash. And, if I may borrow a phrase from you...
And none believe quite so hard as those who have given themselves no other choice.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sees through Lae'zel's fanatacism

Text.Value: Does it matter? I'll be joining him soon enough.
The colony knows we are here. Already I can hear the whispers.

EditorData.NodeContext: Very slight hint of strain, but powering through with wry amusement. A mind flayer colony assaults the minds of any who are not part of the collective, trying to dominate them. But she's been through it before.

Text.Value: The Orphic Hammer. I will admit, I did not expect it to be an actual hammer.

EditorData.NodeContext: We've gained the hammer, which is the key to our plan to save the world. SHe's mildly surprised that this mystical artefact is so literal.

Text.Value: I have fought hollow shells of men who clawed for more life as if it was their gods-given right. And not a one of them would've known what to do with it if they had succeeded.
Let us find Aylin and extend Lorroakan's invitation? It has been too long since I have seen a wizard cry.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 155 - Lorroakan intends to retrieve Nightsong

Text.Value: It is ill-mannered to bite off more than you can chew, my Lord.

EditorData.NodeContext: Unmoved by Astarion's veiled threat to feed on her - she'll shelve it until after we kill the Absolute, but she plans on making sure he doesn't prey on the city

Text.Value: Grandma! Watch your mouth.
You've found a little bit of yourself again. Do not let Selûne take all of the credit - she may have lit the way, but it is you who took the step.
The Grand Duke to be. I'd follow you into battle, Wyll - but politics? I think I am perhaps too faint of heart.

EditorData.NodeContext: Saluting player Wyll's new title with wry amusement, not mocking
EditorData.logicalname: AVATAR Topic 136 - Wyll is now officially going to pursue being Grand Duke in final decision

Text.Value: Play whatever part you must to get us closer to Orin's stone. It is not for me to question.

EditorData.NodeContext: Hushed anger and warning - we're in the Murder Tribunal, pretending to be cold-hearted murderers to infiltrate the cult of Bhaal. She'd rather kill them all but is grudgingly playing along.

Text.Value: We do not know this Prince of the Comet - a thin thread on which to hang all of our hopes.

EditorData.NodeContext: Frustrated shrug - we've decided to trust Orpheus at the eleventh hour
EditorData.logicalname: Topic 131 - Waiting to choose a fate for Orpheus after dealing with Emperor

Text.Value: We still need the illithid. Is that going to be a problem for you?
Come! We'll never bring the Brain low, trapped down here like fledgling chicks.

EditorData.NodeContext: Brief pause in battle, urging us to get higher so we can attack the Brain that hovers above the city

Text.Value: I don't know what else to do, Jaheira.
Then there's two of us.

EditorData.NodeContext: Stop looking for a point in this, because there isn't one - it's just shit and unfair

Text.Value: Eh. Live a little.
I suppose there is something to that.
I had no wish to lose you, Wyll, but - my, it would have been nice to flush her into the colony's flesh-pit.
I had no wish to lose Wyll, but - my, it would have been nice to flush her into the colony's flesh-pit.

EditorData.NodeContext: Gritting her teeth after another encounter with a very haughty Mizora. Referencing the fact that we saved Mizora in the colony in order to save Wyll, but relishing the thought of having left her there.
EditorData.logicalname: Topic 108 - Mizora Wyrm Bridge [AVATAR CHECK ON SUB-NODE]

Text.Value: Its enemies, I trust you mean. And without your hunger, you have little need to feed on living creatures.

EditorData.NodeContext: Correcting Astarion - and clarifying that she'll only tolerate him in the city so long as he reins in his appetite

Text.Value: You know, this might be the easy part. No planning. No doubt. Just the impossible task ahead - so try to have a little fun, yes?

EditorData.NodeContext: Gallows cheer - the odds are against us, but all we can do is fight now

Text.Value: Wyll is a good man, and that is exactly what his devil will use to bind him, in as many ways she knows how.
Good. Perhaps she needs that, too.

EditorData.NodeContext: Not of quiet approval

Text.Value: So ally yourself with Gortash if you see some benefit in it, and we'll reckon with him when we must. It is your Orin you must face, in the end - and your father.
'The Blade of Frontiers'. May the tortured rhymes recounting your deeds continue.

EditorData.NodeContext: Wry amusement, saluting Wyll's choice to keep his title
EditorData.logicalname: Topic 134 - Wyll is now officially Blade of Frontiers in final decision

Text.Value: To slay a devil in his domain is to end him entire. Or - it should be.

EditorData.NodeContext: Not convinced Raphael is actually dead
EditorData.logicalname: Topic 148 - Defeating Raphael in the HoH

Text.Value: I'm not ready to give up on her just yet.
We can speak to Karlach of Avernus later. Let her live in this world a little, while she is able.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sad about the fact that Karlach can only live if she returns to the hells, but not wanting to have that fight tonight, when she's still so happy.

Text.Value: Repeat that mantra. Make of it a prayer, and see if it will save you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Not convinced by our efforts to justify sacrificing SH's parents

Text.Value: I will not lie, and tell you that this does not cause me to doubt. But... it doesn't change anything.

EditorData.NodeContext: Steadying herself - this is all grim, but it doesn't change anything really so long as we are still going to do the right thing.

Text.Value: I was ready to advise you to make common cause with Viconia, if it would have served the city.

EditorData.NodeContext: Quiet anger - she was willing to compromise in order to secure Viconia's help in the final battle, but the player went too far and surrendered Shadowheart to her
EditorData.logicalname: BUILDOUT Topic 111 - Shadowheart Betrayed to Viconia.

Text.Value: It is for her to make the choice, not I.
Shadowheart's choices are her own, but I bear no small blame. Viconia should have been rooted from the city years ago. First the Absolute - then, a reckoning.

EditorData.NodeContext: Resigned pity and regret - feels partly responsible for what befell SH, but won't excuse her for the evil she's done. First we kill the Absolute, THEN we deal with it

Text.Value: The Gur are wise, but they do not know you. They do not believe that you can rise above your hunger - for blood, or power. Please prove them wrong.

EditorData.NodeContext: Urging player-Astarion to be worthy of the faith that's been placed in him

Text.Value: I cannot presume to know your parents, or what they suffered - but I know that they were proud, in the end.

EditorData.NodeContext: SH's parents just died at her hand in a mercy-killing

Text.Value: By the stars, it is probably not even the most foolish cause that has seen mortals rise to divinity.

EditorData.NodeContext: 'by the stars' is akin to 'by the gods'.

Text.Value: Ever will Shar try to twist bonds of love into chains of service. Shadowheart did not let her.

EditorData.NodeContext: Pride in Shadowheart for not letting Shar manipulate her

Text.Value: Yes. As an ally - or occasional opponent - I know him to be an honourable man. He raised you well.
No harm can come to Mizora, Jaheira. I need her.
And if I am? What does it mean?
How are you?
Denying Gortash was the easy part. Come - it is your father we must face, in the end.
This ritual Astarion's spawn-kin spoke of - it seems his master has prepared a homecoming.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sarcastic, note of foreboding - we've just heard of the Black Mass,  a ritual for which Cazador requires Astarion as a sacrifice

Text.Value: Gale has lived under the threat of death for some time, but Orin will make him beg for it - if we give her the time.

EditorData.NodeContext: note of foreboding - our companion might be strong, but Orin will break anyone
EditorData.logicalname: Topic 127 - Orin kidnapped Gale from camp

Text.Value: I have no love for the drow, but she is one of us. We cannot leave her beneath Orin's knife.

EditorData.NodeContext: note of foreboding - our companion might be strong, but Orin will break anyone
EditorData.logicalname: Topic 127 - Orin kidnapped Minthara from camp

Text.Value: I don't know. But if he comes asking for it, I hope you have more to offer him than your judgement alone.

EditorData.NodeContext: Shrugging - she understands why we would be mad with Wyll, but that won't help him

Text.Value: It's possible. You know I don't remember much.
I'll not trust a word that slithers out of Gortash's mouth. I need to hear it from you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Tense, not wanting to believe what she just heard from Gortash - that player is Bhaalspawn / started the Absolute plot. Deep breath, bracing - needs to hear it from us.

Text.Value: You've made your choices. Whatever they have made of you, this city is still your home.

EditorData.NodeContext: Distaste - we're allies for the fight ahead so she has to be pragmatic. But this isn't acceptance- only a temporary truce

Text.Value: Shadowheart has found a little bit of herself again. Selûne cannot take all of the credit - she may have lit the way, but it is the cleric who took the step.
Karlach needs time. Space.

EditorData.NodeContext: Grim. Karlach has just had her revenge on Gortash, who's responsible for the fact that she's going to die soon. Karlach flew into a helpless rage afterwards, realising she can't be cured. She then left for camp to be alone. Jaheira is not pretending to have any answers here - it's stupid and unfair, we can't do anything to stop it, but we should at least do whatever we can.
EditorData.logicalname: Topic 130 - Karlach finished her monologue after Gortash's death, where it became clear she's going to die (Companion)

Text.Value: I cannot presume to know her parents, or what they suffered - but I know that they were proud, in the end.

EditorData.NodeContext: SH's parents just died at her hand in a mercy-killing

Text.Value: Besides, take heart. Your tadpole may yet burst from your skull before it comes to that.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sarcastic cheer, but actually trying to cheer Astarion up. He sacrificed his ability to walk in sunlight for the greater good.

Text.Value: ...I hope that arsehole died afraid.

EditorData.NodeContext: Leaning in quietly, as if trying out a phrase she knows she shouldn't.

Text.Value: So your mysterious artefact, tamer of parasites - is only another parasite itself.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 172 - Learned Daisy is mind flayer

Text.Value: How convenient - that the key to our salvation is the very corruption your illithid friend has been asking you to embrace all along.

EditorData.NodeContext: Grim, dry, not believing a bit of it

Text.Value: You have courage, child of Gith. It is no small thing to turn your back on all the ideals of a lifetime.

EditorData.NodeContext: Impressed with us - we pushed back on Vlaakith, to whom we had been dedicated

Text.Value: Seven thousand souls. Astarion inherits his master's debts as well as his very fine palace. And when all of this is done, I plan on being a very nosey neighbour.

EditorData.NodeContext: Quiet, reflective - just watched Astarion sacrifice thousands of vampire spawn, who died screaming.

Text.Value: Far from me to judge you for playing coy with Mystra. But I will not be cleaning up whatever mess she makes of you for it.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 178 - AVATAR Gale met Mystra, didn't commit to return crown.

Text.Value: He sacrificed his father. Do you really believe he deserves our comfort?
If I thought the city had despoiled the nature above - that harbour water was far from a sparkling blue.

EditorData.NodeContext: Note of disgust - glad to be out of the submersible and out of the harbour water
EditorData.logicalname: Topic 113 - Return from the Iron Throne

Text.Value: But it is not just my life, or that of Orpheus - is it? Do you truly believe your queen will save you, when you are no longer of use to her?
I've spent over a century in this city, and still I cannot be sure there isn't more below the streets than above them.

EditorData.NodeContext: Mute surprise - we've just found a patch of ruined city beneath the city itself

Text.Value: What Karlach needs is for her friends to help her find a cure.

EditorData.logicalname: Alias (AVATAR Topic 138 - Wyll chose to save his father and pact himself eternally to Mizora and Zariel)

Text.Value: Spare me your pity. I saved myself, and that's what matters.
The last time Bhaalspawn walked the world, it was only to serve their father's design. We got lucky in averting it once.
Do you expect me to explain myself to you?
I wish I could. But she alone knows what awaits her in Avernus, and she has made her choice.

EditorData.NodeContext: Firm. Returning to Avernus will save Karlach, but would also return her to slavery. She respects what Karlach wants

Text.Value: Leave Aylin to her sorrow. Likely the wizard only reminds of her of all the other fools, past and present, who have sought to use her.
Choose your words carefully. There is a difference between what is true, and what is right.

EditorData.NodeContext: Denial, doesn't want to hear us embracing our bloodline

Text.Value: No one truly understands the weight of loss until they've worn it a while. There is no shame in sharing the load, when you need to.

EditorData.NodeContext: Shrugging - she broke down after losing her husband in previous games, over 100 years ago.

Text.Value: That preening vulture seems intent on haunting our camp. I suppose we shall find out if her kind sleep - and how heavily.

EditorData.NodeContext: Referring to Mizora lingering at camp. She's just bound Wyll in another pact, using the safe return of his father as leverage.
EditorData.logicalname: AVATAR Topic 138 - Wyll chose to save his father and pact himself eternally to Mizora and Zariel

Text.Value: You deserve a better end than shredding your soul for our sake. But then, this is not a matter of what is deserved.

EditorData.NodeContext: Grim, does not like our decision to sacrifice ourselves and become a mind flayer - but knows it's our only option

Text.Value: I do not mock loyalty. Only mourn when it is given so freely to those so undeserving.
Such... certainty. I hope it sustains you in the days to come.

EditorData.NodeContext: We've pushed back on her commiserations for causing the death of our father - she's not buying it.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 165 - SH freed her parents in Act 3 after abandoning Shar in Act2

Text.Value: All right, now. Watch your language.
'The Blade of Avernus'. I suppose hell is just another frontier.

EditorData.NodeContext: Wry amusement, saluting Wyll's choice to go from 'Blade of Frontiers' to 'Blade of Avernus'
EditorData.logicalname: Topic 135 - Wyll is now officially Blade of Avernus in final decision

Text.Value: What whispers? Are you well?
Lae'zel has courage, turning her back on a lifetime's belief. As for us - best we stay out of interplanar politics, I think. Orpheus is on his own.
You think I was wrong to accept her terms?

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 162 - SH learned truth of parents from NS

Text.Value: If he still believes in you, I would not be overly concerned what your lady love thinks - goddess, or no.

EditorData.NodeContext: Comfort for Gale - Mystra has abandoned him, but Elminster has not. She makes it clear whose opinion she values more.

Text.Value: You can't kill her, Jaheira - she'll escape to Avernus sooner than you could snatch a blade.
We can have our reckoning over the rubble afterwards.

EditorData.NodeContext: Distaste - we're allies for the fight ahead so she has to be pragmatic. But this isn't acceptance- only a temporary truce

Text.Value: The things our companion has done... they might never be set right. But so long as we are still willing to try, then I know I am in the right company.
Hah, a sharper sense than that. That of painful experience.

EditorData.NodeContext: Very slight hint of strain, but powering through with wry amusement. A mind flayer colony assaults the minds of any who are not part of the collective, trying to dominate them. But she's been through it before.

Text.Value: I think Gortash is telling the truth. I've had... dreams.
If he still believes in Gale, the boy should not be overly concerned what his lady love thinks - goddess, or no.

EditorData.NodeContext: Comfort for Gale - Mystra has abandoned him, but Elminster has not. She makes it clear whose opinion she values more.

Text.Value: They say that the only thing a vampire can feel is hunger. Nothing else touches them - not grief, or mercy. Or any sense of what is just.

EditorData.NodeContext: Reflective - note of compassion. She just witnessed Astarion finally get revenge by killing Cazador, and still spare the other vampire spawn rather than sacrificing them to seize Cazador's power for himself. Knows he won't accept a direct compliment, so stating it to the air instead.
EditorData.logicalname: Topic 120 - Companion Astarion faced Cazador, but stayed a vampire spawn.

Text.Value: I wish I could make some sense of all this for you. I cannot. But I do know this.
The wizard is a twit, but he is not a fool. Our ruse will buy only a short reprieve - we ought to tell Dame Aylin.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 153 - Player convinced Lorroakan that NS is dead

Text.Value: I will not be mocked, Harper.
Only to remind you that it is a part.

EditorData.NodeContext: Hushed anger and warning - we're in the Murder Tribunal, pretending to be cold-hearted murderers to infiltrate the cult of Bhaal. She'd rather kill them all but is grudgingly playing along.

Text.Value: I'm more than a simple Sharran now. You may call me Mother Superior.
Do not trust a word that slithers out of Lord Liar's mouth. It suits the cult to have us divided - doubting one another.

EditorData.logicalname: OTHER AVATAR DU, DON'T KNOW BS, POST-GORTASH

Text.Value: All hail the mighty Sharran. A-glow with some victory she cannot even recall.

EditorData.NodeContext: Distaste, but also pity - player-Shadowheart has just been manipulated into sacrificing her parents to Shar, and then had the memory erased

Text.Value: Thank you, Jaheira. I appreciate it.
I thought the Harpers knew every hidey-hole and rat-run in the city. This place housed something slightly larger than a rat, I think.

EditorData.NodeContext: Looking around a massive chamber beneath Wyrm's Crossing

Text.Value: Shadowheart walks a little freer of the shadows. She could shave her skull and paint it purple - it would still suit her.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 163 - SH changed hair after speaking w/Nightsong.

Text.Value: I don't plan on being another Cazador, Jaheira. You have nothing to fear.
If it tries to dominate me, turn me against you... well. I have seen you fight. I'm sure you'll be fine.

EditorData.NodeContext: Very slight hint of strain, but powering through with wry amusement. A mind flayer colony assaults the minds of any who are not part of the collective, trying to dominate them. But she's been through it before.

Text.Value: Don't worry about me, ma'am. Still focused on the fight.
Illithids are monstrous creatures. But... in the end, they are only that. Creatures.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sighing, talking herself around. It's not a good thing that we're working with an illithid, but we have no choice - and in the end, it's just another animal.

Text.Value: You speak from experience?
You might have mentioned you had githyanki gish roiling around in your pocket.

EditorData.NodeContext: Slight reproach, but moving past it.

Text.Value: We'd be fools to retaliate against Cazador by night. But we shouldn't wait long past morning - I doubt the homecoming he plans for Astarion is a happy one.

EditorData.NodeContext: Surveying aftermath of a battle with vampire spawn in which Astarion was kidnapped
EditorData.logicalname: Topic 143 - Vampire spawn attacked the camp during the night and took Astarion

Text.Value: Fuck, yeah.
Well-spoken.

EditorData.NodeContext: Blunt, not to be deflected - Astarion did a noble thing.

Text.Value: And still you signed his contract. Perhaps it was the wiser course, but I have trouble believing our problems can be solved so easily.

EditorData.NodeContext: Not fully questioning our decision to trust Raphael - but coming close

Text.Value: Yes, there is.

EditorData.NodeContext: Blunt, not to be deflected - Astarion did a noble thing.

Text.Value: Me, I think I would have tugged the great goddess' hair a bit first.
Still is, probably. Along with a tadpole that, lest we forget, is just waiting for a chance to split your skull.
It's Shar's victory over the Absolute I think of. Whatever the cost, it was worth it.
All we achieved was sending the devil home - and damning Wyll along with her. It is a lesson worth learning, I think - that this company discards allies so easily.

EditorData.NodeContext: Grim distaste - we just killed Mizora, which dragged our ally Wyll to the hells along with her.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 174 - Netherstone needs Illithid avatar or Karlach

Text.Value: No. I am sorry.
Orin snatches a child to clamour for our attention. She has it.

EditorData.NodeContext: Quiet, restrained anger - but hint of fury beneath. Orin has kidnapped and threatened a child to force us to come to her.

Text.Value: Sorry, Jaheira. That just sounds wrong coming from you.
A few dozen times.

EditorData.NodeContext: Blunt, not to be deflected - Astarion did a noble thing.

Text.Value: That's a fate we'll all share, sooner or later. But speaking as one who has managed to put it off for so long...

EditorData.NodeContext: Not diminishing Karlach's terminal illness, nor giving in to hopelessness - just stating a fact

Text.Value: It wasn't all that quick.
We just played host to an undying queen - and us without our fine silverware.

EditorData.NodeContext: Dry - we just had a large and loud God-Queen imperiously appear in our camp as a hologram - Jaheira did not like her
EditorData.logicalname: BUILDOUT Topic 141 - Vlaakith appeared in camp as a hologram and Lae'zel was on Orpheus path after

Text.Value: But she is alone. She's going to die.
But more than this, I think. She needs to know she is not alone.
If your kind walk the world again... no. No. Doubt between us only serves Gortash - only serves the Absolute.

EditorData.NodeContext: Steadying herself - this is all grim, but it doesn't change anything really so long as we are still going to do the right thing.

Text.Value: Who knows. There is often more ignorance than insight in what 'they' say.

EditorData.NodeContext: Rounding off her praise of Astarion as if it was just an idle thought

Text.Value: Seven thousand souls, Astarion. That is all it cost to inherit your master's power. His position. His very fine palace.

EditorData.NodeContext: Quiet, reflective - just watched Astarion sacrifice thousands of vampire spawn, who died screaming.

Text.Value: This will not end until she ends it.
Do they? Well, there must be something to it, then.
Use the Emperor, as it would use you. Or discard it. My days of doubting you are done.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sigh, shrugging - it's a shit situation, but up to us really.

Text.Value: I wanted to kill him, not become him.
I hoped we'd find another way to free him from his pact.
This ritual your spawn-kin spoke of - it seems your master has prepared a homecoming for you, Astarion.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sarcastic, note of foreboding - we've just heard of the Black Mass,  a ritual for which Cazador requires Astarion as a sacrifice

Text.Value: You speak from experience?
You are a better man than most, to choose what is right even after what Mystra asked of you.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 177  - AVATAR Gale met Mystra, agreed to return crown

Text.Value: Let's not linger long. I have no desire to avail ourselves of a vampire lord's hospitality.

EditorData.NodeContext: Quiet, warning us not to dally in Cazador's palace

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 144 - Learned about the Orphic Hammer
BUILDOUT Topic 142 - Vlaakith appeared in camp as a hologram and was on Vlaakith path after

Text.Value: But if Mizora means to linger with us, I mean to find out if devils do indeed sleep - and just how heavily.

EditorData.NodeContext: Note of threat creeping in - shit-eating Mizora is the cause of all Wyll's grief

Text.Value: In truth - I do not know. I raised them to make their own choices, as your father did you.
Just sweet nothings for now. It tests me - wants to know why I do not carry a tadpole, as you do.

EditorData.NodeContext: Very slight hint of strain, but powering through with wry amusement. A mind flayer colony assaults the minds of any who are not part of the collective, trying to dominate them. But she's been through it before.

Text.Value: Halsin long urged the Harpers not to abandon this land to the curse. I cannot blame him, for being unable to bear it a second time.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 168 - Halsin left, shadowcurse not lifted

Text.Value: The great Orin the Red tugs your sleeve, sulking for attention. She might come to regret it yet.

EditorData.NodeContext: Quiet, restrained anger - but hint of fury beneath. Orin has kidnapped and threatened a companion to force us to come to her.

Text.Value: Know that when all of this is done, I plan on being a very nosey neighbour.

EditorData.NodeContext: Hint of warning - Astarion has ascended as a vampire lord to better face the Absolute, but she'll be watching him.

Text.Value: For whose benefit? It is your Lady who draws power from your pain, not I.

EditorData.NodeContext: Quiet pity

Text.Value: He knows that you are a Bhaalspawn, but he named you more than that. Bhaal's Chosen: one of the very people behind this plot. Is it true?

EditorData.NodeContext: Tense, not wanting to believe what she just heard from Gortash - that player is Bhaalspawn / started the Absolute plot. Deep breath, bracing - needs to hear it from us.

Text.Value: Give me some time. I... need to think.

EditorData.NodeContext: Quiet - this is queueing up the confrontation she has with us at camp.

Text.Value: Spare me your wise counsel, greyling. I did not ask for it.
For your sake, I hope you are right. But I fear you are not.
You plan to become a god now, do you? And all because your lover spurned you.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 179 - AVATAR Gale met Mystra, refused to return crown, wants to be god

Text.Value: The Iron Throne. Named for the sordid cabal of warmongers it was once headquarters to. No wonder Gortash feels at home.

EditorData.NodeContext: Distaste, looking around the repurposed headquarters of a faction she took down many years ago

Text.Value: Oh, you know. Still dying.
We've done what we came to do, and we are all of us sullied for it. Let us make it worth it.

EditorData.NodeContext: Tight-lipped anger, and herself and us. We were masquerading as devotees of Bhaal to gain access to his temple - but we went to far and completed a sacrifice to do it. She'll salvage something from this, but only because not to waste it.
EditorData.logicalname: Topic 184 - Completed the Bhaal Murder Tribunal by obeying Sarevok

Text.Value: I will admit a petty sort of pleasure in your making the goddess look a lackwit, cleric.

EditorData.NodeContext: Amused contempt for Shar

Text.Value: The Gur have been fighting evil longer than this city has stood. It was not for us to gainsay them.

EditorData.NodeContext: Stifling her reservations. We just helped the Gur kill the vampire lord Astarion, having been swayed to believe that he'd gone too far. It doesn't sit well with her to betray an ally, but it's done.

Text.Value: ...I do not know.

EditorData.NodeContext: Steadying herself - this is all grim, but it doesn't change anything really so long as we are still going to do the right thing.

Text.Value: No explanation required. The loyal soldier serves her queen, and receives rewards undying in return.

EditorData.NodeContext: Lightly sarcastic

Text.Value: I believe you. In this very moment, at least. But you might live long enough to forget your promises. The meaning of hunger, pain and fear.

EditorData.NodeContext: Acknowleding that player-Astarion has good intentions for his power as a vampire lord - but warning that she will remain vigilant

Text.Value: Handle the berserker's heart with care, yes? Just because it is made of metal does not mean it cannot be broken.

EditorData.NodeContext: Gentle warning to be nice to Karlach if we're her partner. She's tough, but needs care too

Text.Value: Gale plans to become a god now, does he? And all because his lover spurned him.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 182 - Gale met Mystra, refused to return crown, wants to be god

Text.Value: Welcome back to the world, Karlach. Try not to break it, yes?

EditorData.NodeContext: Fond smile - Karlach just got a treatment that means she can touch thing again

Text.Value: I am sure Wyll knows that - but we would do well to remind him, when his days grow dark.
None of us know every detail of one another's past. But we know who we are now - together.
No notions of heroism put you above human failings. I should know - I've had my share of songs written about me.
Do not trust a word that slithers out of Lord Liar's mouth. It suits the cult to have us divided - doubting one another.

EditorData.logicalname: OTHER AVATAR DU, KNOW BS, POST-GORTASH

Text.Value: Ever will Shar try to twist bonds of love into chains of service. You did not let her.

EditorData.NodeContext: Pride in Shadowheart for not letting Shar manipulate her

Text.Value: The Emperor was an adventurer like us - a protector of the city. That has to count for something... ?
If you can call this living.

EditorData.NodeContext: Very slight hint of strain, but powering through with wry amusement. A mind flayer colony assaults the minds of any who are not part of the collective, trying to dominate them. But she's been through it before.

Text.Value: A man might twist himself into something else, just to escape that collar - but I have no such fears for the Blade.
She's already lost her heart. She deserves better than to have her friends heap happy lies upon her.
Do not force the people of this city to remind you, as you reminded Cazador.

EditorData.NodeContext: Acknowleding that player-Astarion has good intentions for his power as a vampire lord - but warning that she will remain vigilant

Text.Value: Unclean. That thing was in my head.
Come - they've disturbed my first peaceful sleep in a lifetime. Reason enough to be rid of them.

EditorData.NodeContext: Slight reproach, but moving past it. More important things to deal with - the 'they' here being githyanki monks who attacked our camp in the night

Text.Value: But to trade an ally like chattel - you and the Mother Superior make fine bedfellows already.

EditorData.NodeContext: 'you deserve one another'

Text.Value: Harpers are supposed to be virtuous. But if I had my tormentor at my mercy, the means to punish him at hand...

EditorData.NodeContext: Raised eyebrows, reflecting on Astarion choosing to kill Cazador and end the ritual rather than ascending in his place.

Text.Value: Help me convince her to return to Avernus.
It is for you to make sure that is so. And your debt will extend far beyond the end of the Absolute.

EditorData.NodeContext: Correcting Astarion - and clarifying that she'll only tolerate him in the city so long as he reins in his appetite

Text.Value: It is rare to meet so true a believer, child of Gith. Despite reason's every attempt to sway you, you stay your course.

EditorData.NodeContext: Not fully mocking, but eyebrows raised at how staunchly we stick with Vlaakith, who is clearly an asshole

Text.Value: And if it can, a parasite will keep its host fat, happy, and safe. Until it is finished feeding, at least. Am I comforting you? I am not comforting myself.
If you feel you are being watched, take comfort - that is only because you are.

EditorData.NodeContext: Quiet - dry gallows humour. We're in a mind flayer colony, a deadly alien environment. She's been in one before

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 122 - Companion Astarion faced Cazador and became a vampire lord.

Text.Value: I'll soon be skulking from the sun again - there's nothing terribly graceful about that.
Please do - I would love to have you for supper.
That pointy-hatted old fart talks too much. But he has also moved mountains, walked between planes, and dragged himself back from death a dozen times.

EditorData.NodeContext: Wry fondness in 'pointy-hatted far' - she speaks of Elminster,one of the most powerful wizards alive, and an old ally from previous games.

Text.Value: You've learned to choose your own course. Enjoy that dizzying sense of freedom - after comes twice the headaches.

EditorData.NodeContext: Wry warning

Text.Value: Vlaakith will not never stop hunting Prince Orpheus. Can he count on your support?
How do you feel, knowing the cost of keeping your transformation at bay?
Pay me no mind. It is only... this place is familiar, somehow.

EditorData.NodeContext: Shaking head, distracted - we're drawing near the Temple of Bhaal, where she and the party of previous games fought the final battle of BG1.

Text.Value: Cazador is keen to greet his wayward son once more - with open arms, or iron shackles.

EditorData.NodeContext: Dry, understated - we've just been ambushed in the night by vampire spawn who tried to kidnap Astarion.

Text.Value: As I said - it is no small thing.
I try not to play at politics, especially those of another plane. Your prince's battle is his own.
Be wary of Lae'zel. She chose loyalty, yes - but there are none so dangerous as those who only believe because they must.
You've made your choice - and us with you, Silvanus spare us. The princeling will save his people - just not in the way he imagined.

EditorData.NodeContext: Grim resolve - we've decided to sacrifice Orpheus, allowing the Emperor to consume his brain so that we might have the power to defeat the Brain
EditorData.logicalname: Topic 112 - Orpheus Brain consumption / Turning into a mindflayer

Text.Value: Careful, Astarion. Despite your every effort to the contrary, I am in danger of thinking you might be a good man.

EditorData.NodeContext: Wry, knows Astarion will deflect but acknowledging that he did a noble thing.

Text.Value: I will admit a petty sort of pleasure in watching Shadowheart make the goddess look a lackwit.

EditorData.NodeContext: Amused contempt for Shar

Text.Value: Prince Orpheus will die. Don't make me take your life in the bargain.
He named you as Bhaal's Chosen. A Bhaalspawn. Is it true?

EditorData.NodeContext: Tense, not wanting to believe what she just heard from Gortash - that player is Bhaalspawn / started the Absolute plot. Deep breath, bracing - needs to hear it from us.

Text.Value: In another lifetime, I might have stood on the other side of that fight. We can call it a lesser evil, but it did not feel like one.

EditorData.NodeContext: Regret at having been forced to kill the Gur, who wanted to kill Astarion
EditorData.logicalname: TOPIC 151 - Helper Vampire Lord Astarion kill the Gur

Text.Value: I was not always a Harper. I only returned to their fold once I knew it was my own cause I fought for - not whichever one they assigned to me.

EditorData.NodeContext: Shrugging, hinting at some previous crises of faith she had herself. She is a Harper, but she doesn't fight for causes blindly

Text.Value: But - still. I am sorry, Wyll. It is a hard thing to lose someone, and wonder if you might have saved them.

EditorData.NodeContext: Shrugging, knows there is no real comfort and that Wyll will have moments of blaming himself regardless

Text.Value: Why spare her feelings, then? Go to her. Tell her.

EditorData.NodeContext: Slow, quiet contempt for our lack of pity for Karlach.

Text.Value: Far from me to judge Gale for playing coy with Mystra. But I will not be cleaning up whatever mess she makes of him for it.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 181 - Gale met Mystra, didn't commit to return crown.

Text.Value: Come. The great General flees us - but he left a trail to follow.

EditorData.NodeContext: Keen to be on with the hunt - we stand on top of Moonrise Tower, having just forced Ketheric to retreat down into the Colony.

Text.Value: It matters. If you cannot live as you wish, then you can at least die as you choose.
Thank you, for doing what we could not. You and Halsin both.

EditorData.NodeContext: Quiet nod of respect - we didn't lift the curse for her, but she's grateful

Text.Value: Vlaakith will come for Prince Orpheus. Can he count on your support?
Breathe deep - that is the true scent of Baldur's Gate assaulting your nostrils.

EditorData.NodeContext: Wry - we're wandering down in the sewers

Text.Value: Don't cry for vampire spawn. Through me, they might actually serve some good.
Gale is a better man than most, to choose what is right even after what Mystra asked of him.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 180 - Gale met Mystra, agreed to return crown

Text.Value: Whatever time remains to her is precious. She deserves to know just who she is wasting it on.

EditorData.NodeContext: Slow, quiet contempt for our lack of pity for Karlach.

Text.Value: Karlach. Recall that I am an old woman, and you cannot strike me for asking stupid questions.
I want to say yes. But then, I was happy to work with a tainted True Soul when it suited my ends.
Shar believes us so fearful of pain that we would empty our lives of all other feeling just to escape it.

EditorData.NodeContext: Shaking her head at how Shar underestimated Shadowheart
EditorData.logicalname: Topic 164 - SH freed parents after abandoning Shar last miniute

Text.Value: What would your children have done in my place?
Trust me. With the grand wisdom of centuries, I can make no more sense of this than you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Stop looking for a point in this, because there isn't one - it's just shit and unfair

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 146 - Signed the deal with Raphael in SC

Text.Value: The Harpers have known many defeats - but slinking from this land when the shadow-curse first fell was one of our most shameful.

EditorData.NodeContext: Grim regret at her memory of leaving the shadowlands cursed

Text.Value: And afterwards, the reckoning.

EditorData.NodeContext: Quiet promise of future conflict

Text.Value: Oh, do. I would love to have you for supper.
I sometimes wondered if Viconia had returned to the Underdark. But instead she brought her sordid little patch of darkness to the city with her.

EditorData.NodeContext: Reflective after seeing an old ally / enemy in the city. Distaste - Viconia continued on a dark path, and for that Jaheira has only contempt.

Text.Value: You speak as if this place is alive.
Make your choice. Wherever it leads, we will follow.

EditorData.NodeContext: Resignation - but she's trusted us this far, so she'll trust us a little longer

Text.Value: I don't remember what happened, Jaheira. Why don't you tell me?
True. But not half the horror he had earned.

EditorData.NodeContext: Blunt, not to be deflected - Astarion did a noble thing.

Text.Value: Leave.
And when all of this is over, I will hug my children so hard that Rion might kill me from sheer surprise.

EditorData.NodeContext: Wry amusement, trying to take the edge off talk of grief

Text.Value: I think that if I had the chance to snatch someone I loved from the jaws of death, I would not be asking for anyone else's opinion.

EditorData.NodeContext: Not judging Wyll for taking the pact - remembering those she lost, and what she would do in his place

Text.Value: So Shar - and who knows what other gods - fight over the Prism like brats over boiled sweets. And it is the mortal realms that suffer.

EditorData.NodeContext: Disgust at the pettiness of the gods that set this entire conflict in motion.

Text.Value: Undying or not, she was very loud.

EditorData.NodeContext: Vlaakith irritated her

Text.Value: And answers. Justice. Ten years of her life back. All manner of things we cannot give her.

EditorData.NodeContext: Listing all of the many things Karlach deserves but won't get. Not lecturing or bitter. Just knows all our good intentions won't help Karlach, and lying to ourselves about it won't either.

Text.Value: Please.

EditorData.NodeContext: Very slight hint of strain, but powering through with wry amusement. A mind flayer colony assaults the minds of any who are not part of the collective, trying to dominate them. But she's been through it before.

Text.Value: I just wish she'd stop sulking.
He betrayed them, but only in the hopes of saving them. It will comfort the others little to know that.

EditorData.NodeContext: Weary pity. The corpse of the tiefling's disgraced leader just turned up in our camp, a 'gift' from Orin. From a note she left we learn that Zevlor was fooled into joining the cult in the hope it would save his people.

Text.Value: But - should great Vlaakith come to settle a score with Lae'zel, well. I might be convinced to kill her.
'The Steel Foundry builds a brighter future for all'. Unless you happen to work here. Or live nearby. Or require clean air to breathe.

EditorData.NodeContext: Quoting some pamphlet / posters about the Foundry, in contrast to the miserable place it actually is

Text.Value: A colony is a sentience, comprised of the collective. For anything outside of that collective - assimilation, or annihilation.

EditorData.NodeContext: Very slight hint of strain, but powering through with wry amusement. A mind flayer colony assaults the minds of any who are not part of the collective, trying to dominate them. But she's been through it before.

Text.Value: What is this? Some Harperish sixth sense?
May I.

EditorData.NodeContext: Not buying into our bullshit at all

Text.Value: Cazador would have used his power to prey on the city. If you say you will be its protector, instead - I plan to hold you to that standard.

EditorData.NodeContext: Correcting Astarion - and clarifying that she'll only tolerate him in the city so long as he reins in his appetite

Text.Value: I'd rather you focus on our other visitor. You must have met my father before?
The devil's den is every bit as gaudy as I would have imagined.

EditorData.NodeContext: Distaste - unfazed that we're in the Hells, more focused on Raphael's tacky interior design

Text.Value: Better, actually. I know the artefact's true nature, now.
I am not sure I would have the grace to give him such a quick death.

EditorData.NodeContext: Raised eyebrows, reflecting on Astarion choosing to kill Cazador and end the ritual rather than ascending in his place.

Text.Value: Would that there was a hand big enough to smack them all. Meaning no insult, Oakfather Silvanus.

EditorData.NodeContext: Disgust at the pettiness of the gods that set this entire conflict in motion. Last line is a brief flick of the eyes upward, as if correcting herself - she doesn't mean HER god, of course

Text.Value: It is said vampires only make a show of feeling - that their only true emotion is hunger. But those screams sounded real enough.

EditorData.NodeContext: Quiet, reflective - just watched Astarion sacrifice thousands of vampire spawn, who died screaming.

Text.Value: I did not know Duke Ravengard that well - but I'm sure he would not want his son to become slave to Zariel for his sake.

EditorData.NodeContext: Trying to comfort Wyll on his father's death, which might have been avoided by Wyll pacting himself to an archdevil
EditorData.logicalname: BUILDOUT Topic 137 - Wyll chose to sacrifice his father so he could get out of his pact

Text.Value: Careful what you wish for, Jaheira. I have some form in humbling ladies of your vintage.

EditorData.NodeContext: Arc: SH is now in control of the Shar cult. Responding to a threat from veiled threat from Jaheira.

Text.Value: It doesn't matter. I am who I am - now.
What you were, the things you must have done... you cannot set it all to rights. But if you are still willing to try, then I am still with you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Steadying herself - this is all grim, but it doesn't change anything really so long as we are still going to do the right thing.

Text.Value: Baldur's Gate will tremble before us.
Let us leave this place. Your Prism - and its occupant - are safe-guarded for now.

EditorData.NodeContext: Grim. She's just learned our protection from the Absolute stems from a mind flayer. Not pleased, but knows this is not the place or time.
EditorData.logicalname: Topic 46 - In Astral Plane after Emperor

Text.Value: If she cannot have the life she wants, she will at least die as she chooses.

EditorData.NodeContext: Firm. Returning to Avernus will save Karlach, but would also return her to slavery. She respects what Karlach wants

Text.Value: Hope. The very hook from which these devils try to hang us. I have no answers - for you, or for Wyll.

EditorData.NodeContext: Grim, resigned

Text.Value: I suppose we will have to see if this House of Hope is open to visitors.
I have met few as strong as Halsin - but Orin will break him, if we give her the time to do it.

EditorData.NodeContext: note of foreboding - our companion might be strong, but Orin will break anyone
EditorData.logicalname: Topic 126 - Orin kidnapped Halsin from camp

Text.Value: It makes me feel better, at least. If that makes me selfish, then I suppose I am selfish.
Ketheric waits. Let's press on.
Karlach. Respectfully. Shut up.
That's easy for you to say. You've had the chance to live a full life.
I was actually planning to finish the ritual. My knife just slipped.
On second thought, I think I would prefer it if you hit me.
I am still primed to hear some slimy final rhyme from beyond the grave.

EditorData.NodeContext: Not convinced Raphael is actually dead

Text.Value: The great devil grows sloppy. He makes his offer, but only after telling us where to find what we seek. The Orphic Hammer.

EditorData.NodeContext: Not impressed with smarmy Raphael and his show of confidence
EditorData.logicalname: Topic 147 - Refused the deal with Raphael in SC

Text.Value: You are a good man, Wyll - and that is what your devil will use to bind you, in as many ways as she knows how.

EditorData.NodeContext: Praise, but also hint of warning that Wyll is being manipulated

Text.Value: Grand Duke, is it? I'd follow Wyll into battle, sure enough - but politics? I think I am perhaps too faint of heart.

EditorData.NodeContext: Saluting Wyll's new title with wry amusement, not mocking
EditorData.logicalname: Topic 136 - Wyll is now officially going to pursue being Grand Duke in final decision

Text.Value: It feels... right, somehow. True.
I never met Zevlor, but the way his people spoke of him... hatred, but grief as well. For the man they thought he was.

EditorData.NodeContext: Weary pity. The corpse of the tiefling's disgraced leader just turned up in our camp, a 'gift' from Orin. From a note she left we learn that Zevlor was fooled into joining the cult in the hope it would save his people.

Text.Value: But, should great Vlaakith come to settle a score with you - I suppose I could be convinced to kill her.

EditorData.NodeContext: Cares nothing for githyanki politics, but will fight for us personally if she ahs to

Text.Value: We draw near to the beast's den - where it will be most desperate. I need no tadpole to feel that much.

EditorData.NodeContext: Grim determination - we're getting close to the brain

Text.Value: Lae'zel will not break easily - but Orin will only enjoy her work the more for that, if we give her the time.

EditorData.NodeContext: note of foreboding - our companion might be strong, but Orin will break anyone
EditorData.logicalname: Topic 125 - Orin kidnapped Lae'zel from camp

Synopsis: Jaheira's Topical Greetings. TGs are custom greetings in which companions respond to an event that has just occurred. In some cases, the topic is warrants some brief discussion before looping back to our regular topics.
